<inglise> REGULATION (EEC) No 903/74 OF THE COMMISSION of 17 April 1974 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1726/70 on the procedure for granting the premium for leaf tobacco as regards methods of payment </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 903/74, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1726/70 (lehttubaka jaoks lisatasu andmise korra kohta) seoses maksmisviisidega, 17. aprill 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 727/70 (1) of 21 April 1970 on the common organization of the market in raw tobacco, as last amended by the Act (2) concerning the Conditions of Accession and the Adjustments to the Treaties, and in particular the first subparagraph of Article 3 (3) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 727/70 toortubakaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud &uuml;hinemistingimusi ja asutamislepingutesse tehtavaid muudatusi k&auml;sitleva aktiga, (2) eriti selle artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 3 esimest l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1726/70 (3), in order to take account of the fact that the first processing and market preparation of tobacco are sometimes very lengthy operations, made it possible for the premium to be paid wholly or partly in advance and allowed the Member States to choose between the two methods of payment; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: silmas pidades asjaolu, et tubaka esmane t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine ja pakendamine v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;nikord olla v&auml;ga pikajaalised protsessid, v&otilde;imaldatakse m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1726/70 (3) maksta lisatasu osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult ettemaksena ning lubatakse liikmesriikidel valida kahe maksmisviisi vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the light of the experience that has been gained, it appears that the Member States could meet the needs of the various types of purchaser better if they were also able to use both methods of payment at once; whereas that Regulation should therefore be amended accordingly; </inglise>
<eesti> saadud kogemust silmas pidades ilmneb, et liikmesriigid suudavad paremini vastata eri t&uuml;&uuml;pi ostjate vajadustele, kui nad kasutavad sama ajal m&otilde;lemat makseviisi; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks nimetatud m&auml;&auml;rust vastavalt muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the Opinion of the Management Committee for Tobacco, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las tubakaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The first subparagraph of Article 7 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1726/70 is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1726/70 artikli 7 l&otilde;ike 2 esimene l&otilde;ik asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "2. </inglise>
<eesti> "2. </eesti>
<inglise> The amount of the premium referred to in (1) 2 of the premium certificate shall be advanced on application by the purchaser, in accordance with one or both of the following methods of payment, as chosen by the Member State: " </inglise>
<eesti> Lisatasu sertifikaadi punkti 1 alapunktis 2 osutatud lisatasu summa makstakse ette ostja taotlusel, kasutades iga liikmesriigi valikul &uuml;hte v&otilde;i m&otilde;lemat j&auml;rgmistest maksmisviisidest:" </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 (4) is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 7 l&otilde;ige 4 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "4. </inglise>
<eesti> "4. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall inform the Commission whether it has chosen to apply one or both of the methods of payment". </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad komisjonile, kas nad on valinud kohaldamiseks &uuml;he v&otilde;i m&otilde;lemad maksmisviisid." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
